At Lakelaw we're specialized, but not too specialized. We focus our work of course, on the areas of bankruptcy and foreclosure defense. But bankruptcy and foreclosure defense in Chicago frequently takes us other places. What do I mean by that? Lots of times, people want to prepare to avoid bankruptcy, and so they would like to protect their assets. Asset protection requires estate planning, and so we do a little bit of that.

In addition, sometimes people are not concerned so much about asset protection for bankruptcy, but asset protection in the event of their getting older. They want to protect themselves for Medicaid purposes. Elder law has become an area where we practice as well.

Another thing that we found out was that bankruptcy and probate have a lot in-common. Why? Probate is basically bankruptcy for dead people. It involves a special code, the probate code, a special court, the probate court, and wills and trusts and estates are not so different than bankruptcy plans. The knowledge that we have in bankruptcy has helped us in probate.

Then, in the mortgage foreclosure field, we find that we have been involved in the buying and selling of real estate. Well, buying and selling of real estate short sales requires that we do some real estate transactions. In bankruptcy, we buy and sell assets all of the time, so you have to have asset purchases and sales. We know small businesses. We can start them up, and we can close them down too. Sometimes, when we represent not-for-profit organizations, we help organize those and close them down too.

Even though we are a firm that focuses on bankruptcy and foreclosure defense, you will find that there are many other things that we do that might be helpful to you. We'd like to think of you as our clients, and we'd like to think of us as your lawyers. So if something else comes up that's not something that we do particularly, let us know.

We know people that are the best of the best in every area of law, and we will find them, put them on your case, and make sure they do what's supposed to be done for you.
title: Chicago Bankruptcy Lawyer | David Leibowitz | (847) 249-9100 | LakeLaw.com | Fiduciary

Three passengers died. The cause of the accident is disputed, as many irregularities were later revealed by the accident investigation. This was the first ever crash involving an Airbus A320.

Grupo: La Maravillosa Orquesta del Alcohol
Canción: Nómadas
Grabado y mezclado por Kaki Arkarazo en Gárate Estudios
Producción y mandolina: Diego Galaz
Realización y montaje: Miguel Ángel Cámara y Julio César Cordero (La Navaja Suiza)

Contratación: Black Izar (blackizar@gmail.com)

La Maravillosa Orquesta del Alcohol es un original sexteto que mezcla música acústica e instrumentos como acordeón, banjo, mandolina y saxofón. Con un sonido que bebe del folk, el blues y el rock & roll, esta banda burgalesa (también conocidos como La M.O.D.A) lleva 2 años sin parar de hacer canciones y actuando por todo el país: en festivales, como teloneros de artistas internacionales (Dropkick Murphys, Frank Turner), en salas, bares o en la calle.

Tras casi 70 conciertos y 14 canciones publicadas, el grupo sacará en otoño de 2013 su primer larga duración bajo el sello 'Mús Records', con el productor Diego Galaz y el ingeniero Kaki Arkarazo (Los Coronas, Vetusta Morla, Loquillo) a los mandos. 'Nómadas' es el primer single de adelanto de su nuevo disco y viene acompañado de un videoclip grabado durante su última aventura: una semana de conciertos callejeros por Francia. (Diario de gira: http://www.mondosonoro.com/Entrevista/LA-MARAVILLOSA-ORQUESTA-DEL-ALCOHOL/Diario-de-una-gira-en-camiseta/4381.aspx)

Este nuevo vídeo ha sido llevado a cabo por Miguel Ángel Cámara (erassmuss) y Julio César Cordero, quienes ya realizaron su anterior clip ('Gasoline').
title: La Maravillosa Orquesta del Alcohol (La M.O.D.A) - 'Nómadas'

World's Largest Dog Walk! The Dumb Friends League Furry Scurry is an annual two-mile walk for animals that takes place at Denver's Washington Park on the first Saturday in May. 
(This Footage is a Small Part of the Big Event Video - To watch, visit http://www.YouTube.com/AboutColoradoTV)

A fun game for dog
Does your dog love to chase? Would you like to give your dog more exercise by way of a fun game? Run Dog Run Lure Chasing is what you and your dog have been looking for.

Run Dog Run Lure Chasing offers various pricing options for your dog to run, chase, and play. For 1st time dogs, we allow a free short test run to determine their interest level in the fun game of lure chasing. While most dogs absolutely love to chase the lure because of their natural prey instincts, unfortunately, some dogs may not show any interest at all in this game. Lure chasing is similar to most games, so you will probably see quite an improvement in chasing the lure as your dog learns after a few runs. Once your dog shows its love for the game, you should consider purchasing volume run punch card tickets. Runs on your punch card ticket may be used for any of our non fundraiser run days, plus you can share them with other dog owners. You don't have to use all of your run punches the day you purchase your card. Punch card tickets are also a great gift idea for dog owners!

3 Run Punch Card Ticket = $20
5 Run Punch Card Ticket = $30

As the Dumb Friends League's largest annual fundraiser, more than 12,000 people and 5,000 dogs join us for the walk and raise funds for the homeless pets in our care. The Furry Scurry has become a tradition for many Denver-area residents.

description:
http://www.gaviningham.com/sales-juice-video-sales-training/. In this  funny sales clip we look at what differentiates top sales superstars from mediocre wannabes.  

What is it that differentiates a top sales performer from a mediocre one? Why is it that one salesperson will get consistent results no matter what the marketplace and another will consistently struggle?

"If they're not going to buy then I can't really doing anything, can I?" - Kevin.

If you want to reach clients, if you want to differentiate yourself from your competition, if you want to get clients to talk to you, to engage with you, if you want to get into a proper relationship with your clients then you have to be at a "10".

"I was feeling a bit rough on account of a few shandy tops I had with the lads last night" - Wayne

This isn't just a selling thing, this is a personal thing. A lot of people are motivated from the outside in i.e. they allow people, events and circumstances to effect the way that they feel. If you're motivated from the outside in, you're going to struggle to make sure that you're at a "10".

And this is what we see... people arriving at work not on a "10" gradually spiraling out of control... or maybe people starting at a "10" and maybe they lose a sale and from that moment on... they start to be outside in motivated.

"Yes, yes and thrice yes. I can do all of these things better. I am the man. I am the Wayne-meister." - Wayne.

But it's one thing saying these things and another actually doing them! The critical thing is not whether you succeed or not but how you get yourself back up again and give it another try.

In this clip... 

Motivational sales tips for helping you to achieve more success in selling, cold calling, making sales presentations and acing sales pitches.

"I know we will win this business and I will add real value for this client." - Tiff.

Featuring Tom Bennett, Laura Aikman, Ewen Macintosh, Gavin Ingham.
title: Mastering Sales Motivation & Mindset - Sales Tips For Success

description:
Subscribete a nuestro canal aqui: http://full.sc/Opz5LC Subscribe here!

Aqui vemos diversas especies de coaítes (en idioma guaraní, literalmente "nariz larga"), pizotes, cusumbes, cuchuchos, guaches, atones o gatos solos (Nasua) en el entorno natural de la selva que comparten Brasil y Argentina. Se observan tanto coatí de cola anillada, sudamericano o mundi (Nasua nasua) como coatí de nariz blanca (Nasua narica).

Estos animales están acostumbrados a la presencia humana en su ámbito natural, en aquellas lugares en que coincide con  los Parques Nacionales de la zona, y por eso no son difíciles de ver. Lamentablemente sus costumbres están algo alteradas debido a la presencia de alimentos que no le son naturales, llevados por los turistas, y pese a las restricciones y advertencias de que no se los alimente, cosa que algunos igualmente hacen arriesgándose incluso a ser mordidos. Una de las consecuencias de esta actitud es que estos animales, normalmente huidizos e inofensivos, se pueden volver agresivos con el ser humano para conseguir la comida artificial traida por estos a lo que era su hábitat exclusivo, ahora invadido por "homo sapiens".

--ENGLISH--
Here we see several species of South American Coati ("coati" in Guarani language, literally  "long nose") or Ring-tailed Coati (Nasua nasua) in the natural jungle environment shared by Brazil and Argentina.  Are observed both ring-tailed coati (Nasua Nasua) and white-nosed coati (Nasua narica).

These animals are accustomed to human presence in those places that coincide with national parks area, and therefore are not difficult to see.

--PORTUGUES--
Aqui podemos ver várias espécies de quatis ou coatís (na língua guarani, literalmente "nariz longo") no ambiente de floresta natural compartilhado por Brasil e Argentina. Estes animais estão habituados à presença humana nesses lugares que coincidem com parques nacionais nesta área, e, portanto, não são difíceis de ver. Infelizmente, seus costumes são um pouco alterada pela presença de alimentos que não são naturais, impulsionada pelos turistas e apesar das restrições e advertências de que não há que alimentarlos, arriscando-se a ser mordido. São observados tanto quatis-de-cauda-anelada ou quati-mundi (Nasua nasua) como quatis-de-nariz-branco (Nasua narica).

Uma conseqüência desta atitude com estes quatis, geralmente inofensivos, é que eles podem tornar-se agressivos com os seres humanos para obter alimento artificial apresentado por eles no que foi seu habitat original, agora invadidas por "homo sapiens".
title: Coatíes (Nasua) - Quatis - South American Coati

description:
Recorded on the final ever winter event; I never did find that invisible yak making all those suggestive moo noises... 

I'm using a special build for these races; Super Speed, Super Jump, Acrobatics (for mid air movement) and Sprint all 6 slotted for speed, but not jumping as you want to stay in contact with the snow as much as possible.

If you wanted a realistic shot at the badges, you needed to stay on the left, as it shortens the course enough to beat the Gold standard. The right was also quite tough on the first leap (see my other video illustrating that path) which could ruin the entire run if you klutzed it too.

This isn't quite a perfect run, I don't hold racing lines well enough, but pretty close to optimal times; I think maybe 45 seconds was possible, but I recorded this just for posterities sake rather than pride; I'd buy a month of City of Heroes most winters just to moo-goof around on this atmospheric and dear to me map... Goodbye, Pocket D and Ski Chalet... goodbye mysterious floating truck in the distance. Au revoir invisible moo maker. Toodle pip Paragon City. *sniffles*
title: City Of Heroes Winter Event, Slalom, Left Hand Course

description:
Buy Peppermint Tea: http://bit.ly/1tn5vcu 
Peppermint to be the strongest anti-spasmodic and pain reliever of all the herbs, and when an attack flares I really appreciate its noticeable whole-body mild anesthetic effect as well. On a daily basis I find it more effective (and certainly more enjoyable) than prescription anti-spasmodic drugs, particularly when it's brewed as a very strong tea.

In fact, peppermint is such a powerful muscle relaxant that it can trigger GERD (Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease) or heartburn in people who are susceptible. If you are prone to these upper GI problems, avoid mint and stick to the other IBS herbs and spices such as high volatile oil fennel or ginger.

One of the easiest and most effective way to use peppermint for IBS is to brew it (fresh or dried) with boiling water into hot tea (do not actually boil the herb in water as this can destroy its volatile oils, and thus its effectiveness). Peppermint, however, is available in several other beneficial forms as well.

Enteric-coated peppermint oil capsules can be taken before meals to help prevent IBS symptoms. These capsules have been proven highly effective (and safe) in several clinical trials, including studies that focused specifically on children with IBS. These capsules are specially coated so they don't dissolve in the stomach (which could trigger heartburn); instead, they dissolve in the intestines, where they act as a smooth muscle relaxant and pain killer.
title: Peppermint Tea - Help for Irritable Bowel Syndrome; Peppermint Tea Ibs

description:
IT'S NOT RACIST !!!!
----------------------------
Really, it's just a fun little episode from a harmless schoolgirl anime, for god's sake!
If anything, the author of the manga pokes fun at his fellow countrymen for their lack of experience with foreigners.

It's funny. It's harmless .... I really don't understand why so many people go "BLOODY RACIST JAPS" and all that shit!
If you really think so then fucking stop watching anime!

----------------------

This is a scene from the anime "Azumanga Daioh".

Kagura wants to help a man carrying a heavy suitcase.
But - gods help her - that guy is a foreigner (thats next to being an alien from outer space for many xenophobic japanese).
Despite that she manages to communicate (in a sense) in english using hand and feet.
Her english teacher Yukari watches all this to her amusement and targets the next gaijin to show her how you do it properly.
title: Crap, it's a foreigner

description:
-Tumor benígno intradural-extramedular.
-Na maioria das casuísticas de neoplasias do canal espinhal, medula espinhal e leptomeninges, os meningiomas compreendem 25%. A incidência de meningiomas múltiplos é pequena quando comparada com sua freqüência isolada. Na maioria dos casos, a ocorrência múltipla é intracraniana e espinhal. Meningiomas múltiplos localizados exclusivamente no canal raqueano são extremamente raros
O termo meningioma é o nome para tumor nas meninges (tecido que reveste a superfície exterior do cérebro), que geralmente são benignos. Eles podem variar muito no tamanho, de poucos milímetros a muitos centímetros. Os sintomas são causados pela compressão do cérebro ou canal vertebral.
Os meningiomas constituem 10 % dos tumores intracranianos. São mais comuns entre os quarenta e sessenta anos de vida e em mulheres.
A causa do meningioma é desconhecida. Alguns fatores podem influenciar na formação do tumor, como radiação, principalmente em crianças; após uma fratura; pacientes com a Síndrome Von Recklinghausen também tendem a desenvolver vários meningiomas; além de fatores hormonais.
Os meningiomas podem ser detectados através de radiografia de crânio. A TC mostra o tumor como uma massa homogênea densa e bem delimitada. A RMN com contraste demonstra a relação entre o meningioma com as estruturas vascular e neural. E finalmente, a angiografia, demonstra se há a vascularização do tumor.
As opções de tratamento incluem observação, cirurgia e radiação. Tumores pequenos, em pessoas idosas sem sintomas, podem ser observados por RMs anuais. Como esses tumores são benignos e de crescimento lento, eles podem não causar nenhum problema para o paciente.

-Edson Zerati, MD
http://www.edsonzerati.com.br
title: Meningeoma Torácico-Thoracic Meningioma

description:
Did your parents or teachers ever tell you as a kid, "Be careful who you hangout with because they have a major influence on who you become?"  

Well that was just one little part to the formula of who we become.  Although, it that does play a major part since there are only three. 

We are a byproduct of these simple things. When you hear what they are they are almost to simple that we practically ignore the effects that it can truly have on our lives.

An old mentor shared with me a simple formula for shaping whom you become or who we have become today. This formula made me really look at my life objectively. I began to take inventory of these three simple things and I realized that were true and universal principles. What is fascinating is that most people don't realize that they are in full affect in their current live.

Here are the three things that shape who we are and what we can become in the future.

1. The people we associate with (Do you want the lifestyle of the people you associate with? Are they challenging you to become better? Who is on your current speed dial on your cell phone?)
2. The books we read (Most people stop reading books after high school.)
3. The trainings and events we attend. (Are you getting yourself in a position to re-sharpen the saw, or to better master your craft or your increasing your value?)

My challenge for you is; take inventory and make adjustments so that you are living the life you truly want to live.

"Create Your Waves and Live Your Dreams"
DagoZuniga.com
DifferenceDream.com
title: We Are A ByProduct Of These Three Things by Dago Zuniga

description:
E mail: pauloanibal@yahoo.com.br
Seu nome científico é Achatina fulica, foi introduzido ilegalmente no Brasil inicialmente no estado do Paraná há cerca de 20 anos atrás como alternativa econômica ao escargot.O fracasso das tentativas de comercialização levou os criadores, por desinformação,a soltar os caramujos em nossas matas.Como se reproduz rapidamente e não possui predadores naturais aqui no Brasil, hoje tornou-se uma praga agrícola e pode ser encontrado em praticamente todo o país,inclusive nas regiões litorâneas,como no litoral sul do estado de São Paulo,onde constatamos sua maciça invasão.Esse caramujo africano,de fato pode transmitir ao homem os vermes causadores de um tipo de meningite e da peritonite, por ser  o hospedeiro natural deles.
Por Paulo Anibal G. Mesquita
title: Caramujo Achatina fulica

description:
http://www.cardiodynamics.com If you are worried about possible symtoms of hypertension, heart disease, diabetes or cancer then get a Cardio Dynamics screening where you can be tested for possible symptoms and see if you are at risk. Preventive medicine and pre-screening is the best way to aviod serious health problems.

CardioDynamics (NASDAQ: CDIC) was incorporated in 1993 and is committed to fundamentally changing drug management with ICG. The Company's primary product, the BioZ®, uses proprietary Impedance Cardiography (ICG) technology to noninvasively assess a patient's hemodynamics, data which typically has been unavailable in the physician's office and available on a limited basis in the hospital only through a time-consuming, costly, and potentially dangerous invasive procedure called Pulmonary Artery Catheterization (PAC), or the Swan Ganz Catheter.

Since the BioZ's ICG monitoring is noninvasive, it can be performed in outpatient areas such as physician offices, which have never before had access to hemodynamic information in treating heart failure, high blood pressure, pacemaker, and dialysis patients.

For more information on Cardio Dynamics and the ICG Company visit their website for a list of physicians at www.cardiodynamics.com or email Danielle atdogle@cdic.com
title: Preventing and Diagnosing Hypertension with Cardio Dynamics ICG Technology

The aggressive all terrain design is engineered to provide outstanding performance in on-road and off-road driving, and in fact scored a 94.8 for dry handling on dry roads.

The Cooper Discoverer M+S is a great value tire for light truck owners driving in winter conditions. It’s rigorous and detailed testing like this that makes Canadian Tire, Canada’s Automotive Authority.

About USA Basketball
Based in Colorado Springs, Colo., USA Basketball is a nonprofit organization and the national governing body for men's and women's basketball in the United States. As the recognized governing body for basketball in the U.S. by the International Basketball Federation (FIBA) and the United States Olympic Committee (USOC), USA Basketball is responsible for the selection, training and fielding of USA teams that compete in FIBA sponsored international competitions, as well as for some national competitions.

During the 2009-12 quadrennium, 1,273 men and women players and 235 coaches participated in USA Basketball, including USA Basketball Teams, USA Basketball trials and the USA Basketball 3x3 FIBA championships.

USA Basketball men's and women's teams between 2009-12 compiled an impressive 264-35 win-loss record in FIBA and FIBA Americas competitions, the Pan American Games, the World University Games, the Nike Hoop Summit and in exhibition games. 

USA teams are the current men's and women's champions in the Olympics; men's and women's FIBA World Championships (Basketball World Cup); men's and women's FIBA U19 World Championship; men's and women's FIBA U17 World Championships; men's and women's U18 and U16 FIBA Americas Championships, and FIBA 3x3 Women's World Championship and FIBA 3x3 Women's U18 World Championship.  USA Basketball also currently ranks No. 1 in all five of FIBA's world ranking categories, including combined, men's, women's, boys and girls.

For more information, as well as all the latest USA Basketball news and highlights, log onto  its  official website at http://www.USAB.com

description:
If we had the opportunity to start from scratch, even in a space of 8 meters by 10 meters, how would we do it?

How serious is the entirety of human civilization? Four intrepid individuals begin with a blank stage and gleefully rebuild life as we know it. Their tools include mind melds, pickaxes, microphones, electric guitars, and four-part harmony.

Ingeniously remaking social codes, laws of physics, philosophy, music, and human communication, Germinal posits the theory that human civilization may be just one big theater trick.

This layered study in theater magic is one of the most talked-about shows on the international arts circuit.

SEE IT LIVE!
On the Boards, Seattle WA
Sep 25 - 28, 2014

INFO & TICKETS: http://www.ontheboards.org/performances/germinal
